Lips well developed and transversely ellipsoidal. Lower lip reaching or almost reaching transverse line between gill openings, its inner surface covered with numerous small papillae. Maxillary barbel short with free tip. Mouth large. Teeth long, very slender, bicuspid, and curved inward distally; mesial cusp similar in length and form to lateral cusp (
Fig. 2a
). Dentary teeth usually not overlapping medially. Dentary ramus flat, straight, and approximately forming a straight angle (usually ranging from 160° to 180°).
